1
00:00:25,392 --> 00:00:28,190
<i>[Alarm Blaring]</i>

2
00:00:44,878 --> 00:00:46,869
[Chattering]

3
00:02:01,855 --> 00:02:04,653
[Man]
Why should I trust an American?

4
00:02:04,724 --> 00:02:07,318
You killed my wife,
my two daughters,

5
00:02:07,393 --> 00:02:10,829
my son, my father in an air raid.

6
00:02:10,897 --> 00:02:14,560
Well, that wasn't me, old buddy.
I'm just here to make a living.

7
00:02:14,634 --> 00:02:17,125
A case of mistaken identity
right there.

8
00:02:27,113 --> 00:02:29,843
Here's the program.
You hand it to this guy in dubai.

9
00:02:29,916 --> 00:02:32,384
Then he gives you
half a million dollars.

10
00:02:32,452 --> 00:02:34,647
No wire transfers,
no bank files,

11
00:02:34,721 --> 00:02:36,052
no paper trail.

12
00:02:36,122 --> 00:02:38,249
<i>Everybody gets rich.</i>

13
00:02:38,324 --> 00:02:41,521
Granny's still out there
on the porch sipping a lemonade.

14
00:02:49,435 --> 00:02:50,766
No deal.

15
00:02:53,573 --> 00:02:55,939
What do you say?

16
00:02:56,009 --> 00:02:58,409
There's half a mil
looking at you right there.

17
00:03:04,617 --> 00:03:08,610
I'm just a one-man relief agency here.
You guys don't want to play ball.

18
00:03:08,688 --> 00:03:11,384
I know what you really want.

19
00:03:11,457 --> 00:03:12,583
<i>[Gunshot]</i>

20
00:03:40,954 --> 00:03:42,945
Come on.

21
00:03:49,862 --> 00:03:51,853
Come on.

22
00:04:00,173 --> 00:04:02,164
[Whispers]
Where are ya?

23
00:04:08,147 --> 00:04:11,310
Stop. Walid. Stop.
[Speaks Foreign Language]

24
00:04:11,384 --> 00:04:13,648
Walid.

25
00:04:15,688 --> 00:04:18,156
Drop your weapon.

26
00:04:18,224 --> 00:04:20,158
<i>Come on. Don't be stupid.</i>

27
00:04:20,226 --> 00:04:22,490
<i>Turn around.
Drop your weapon, Walid.</i>

28
00:04:22,562 --> 00:04:24,553
Drop it!

29
00:04:24,631 --> 00:04:27,464
Drop it.

30
00:04:27,533 --> 00:04:29,933
I know why you are here.

31
00:04:34,073 --> 00:04:35,938
<i>[Walid Panting]
Walid.</i>

32
00:04:36,009 --> 00:04:37,943
God is great.

33
00:04:49,155 --> 00:04:51,851
Stupid.

34
00:05:07,540 --> 00:05:09,565
<i>[ Dog Barking In Distance]</i>

35
00:05:12,412 --> 00:05:14,642
<i>[Woman Screams]
No.! No.!</i>

36
00:05:14,714 --> 00:05:18,241
[Laughing]
Don't.
Ah, there you go, Mom. Whoo!

37
00:05:18,318 --> 00:05:21,116
Oh, my God.
Oh, my God.

38
00:05:21,187 --> 00:05:23,553
What are you? Cra...
It's disgusting. Get out.

39
00:05:23,623 --> 00:05:25,420
<i>- Get...
[Squeals]
- [Phone Rings]</i>

40
00:05:25,491 --> 00:05:27,391
<i>Get out! You freak.
Jump in.</i>

41
00:05:37,236 --> 00:05:38,828
<i>[Phone Ringing]</i>

42
00:05:40,773 --> 00:05:42,764
Hello.

43
00:05:42,842 --> 00:05:45,106
<i>I need to know what you're wearing.</i>

44
00:05:46,679 --> 00:05:50,115
What am I wearing?
Sweaty T-shirt and jeans.

45
00:05:50,183 --> 00:05:52,048
Old sweater.
[Chuckles]

46
00:05:52,118 --> 00:05:54,450
Hey. How'd the move go?

47
00:05:54,520 --> 00:05:57,182
You know.
It... It's done anyway.

48
00:05:57,256 --> 00:06:02,592
One of the trucks didn't show up,
and they broke the legs off
my poor old console table.

49
00:06:02,662 --> 00:06:06,257
- You're kidding.
- Yeah, I couldn't find the key
to get in when we got here.

50
00:06:06,332 --> 00:06:08,766
Oh.
But we're in.

51
00:06:08,835 --> 00:06:11,235
<i>That's good.
How was your day?</i>

52
00:06:11,304 --> 00:06:13,204
Mmm, interesting.

53
00:06:13,272 --> 00:06:18,642
<i>Good interesting or ''run screaming
out of there with your hair standing up
on your head''interesting?</i>

54
00:06:20,012 --> 00:06:23,072
A little bit of both.

55
00:06:23,149 --> 00:06:27,518
<i>- How's the kid?
- New school, new house,
new friends to make.</i>

56
00:06:27,587 --> 00:06:30,488
<i>He misses L.A.
He misses his girlfriend.</i>

57
00:06:30,556 --> 00:06:34,720
Ah.
I wouldn't buy him a pair of
hundred-dollar sneakers.

58
00:06:34,794 --> 00:06:37,262
You're not here.

59
00:06:37,330 --> 00:06:39,321
<i>[Men Chattering]</i>

60
00:06:40,566 --> 00:06:42,557
How are you doing, sweetie?

61
00:06:43,636 --> 00:06:46,002
I miss you, you know.
But I'm hanging in.

62
00:06:46,072 --> 00:06:49,508
<i>Hey, Mike.
Found our guy.</i>

63
00:06:49,575 --> 00:06:51,236
Mike?

64
00:06:51,310 --> 00:06:53,471
<i>Fazal.
Okay. Hey, babe,
I'm right here.</i>

65
00:06:53,546 --> 00:06:56,037
Uh, listen, I'm gonna...

66
00:06:56,115 --> 00:06:58,606
I'll call you in a bit.
Okay, I gotta go.

67
00:06:58,684 --> 00:07:00,618
Call me later?
All right, babe.

68
00:07:00,686 --> 00:07:03,246
Okay.
Love you. Bye.
Bye. Bye.

69
00:07:18,070 --> 00:07:21,437
- Hey. Tyler, I'm getting you a towel,
and you're getting out.
- Whoo!

70
00:07:21,507 --> 00:07:23,668
<i>[Screams]
[Laughs]</i>

71
00:07:23,743 --> 00:07:25,734
<i>You're dead.</i>

72
00:07:44,130 --> 00:07:46,155
[Man]
Stop the winch!
Stop the winch!

73
00:07:46,232 --> 00:07:48,564
<i>Wayne, look at this.</i>

74
00:07:58,878 --> 00:08:01,870
Get belowdecks.
Get the hell below.

75
00:08:10,022 --> 00:08:13,253
<i>[Man]
Moving house is the number two cause
of mental breakdowns after bereavement.</i>

76
00:08:13,326 --> 00:08:15,260
<i>[Mike]
Oh, is that right?</i>

77
00:08:15,328 --> 00:08:18,422
<i>Number three is what we're doing...
chasing a low-level player
all over the boonies...</i>

78
00:08:18,498 --> 00:08:20,432
<i>when we could let
his own people handle him.</i>

79
00:08:20,500 --> 00:08:22,491
Let me do this my way. Okay?

80
00:08:22,568 --> 00:08:24,559
Guys, stay alert.

81
00:08:24,637 --> 00:08:27,003
<i>[ Chattering In Foreign Language]</i>

82
00:08:31,911 --> 00:08:34,709
[Chattering Continues]

83
00:08:37,250 --> 00:08:39,684
<i>[Mike]
Whoa. Whoa.</i>

84
00:08:39,752 --> 00:08:42,186
[Foreign Language]

85
00:08:44,657 --> 00:08:46,852
[Foreign Language]
[Mike]
I don't understand. What?

86
00:08:46,926 --> 00:08:49,554
He killed my brother.
Ah. Okay, you speak English.

87
00:08:49,629 --> 00:08:53,759
He killed my brother,
and he hang him upside down
and he cut his, uh, belly.

88
00:08:53,833 --> 00:08:55,357
<i>[Man Speaking Foreign Language]</i>

89
00:08:55,434 --> 00:08:57,698
Okay. There's a better way
to do this.

90
00:08:57,770 --> 00:09:01,433
This is my way. Move.
Okay.

91
00:09:01,507 --> 00:09:03,771
Just let me have this one.
Just one. This guy.

92
00:09:03,843 --> 00:09:06,038
[Foreign Language]

93
00:09:07,446 --> 00:09:09,073
<i>No.</i>

94
00:09:09,148 --> 00:09:10,911
[Foreign Language]

95
00:09:13,819 --> 00:09:17,653
You want him, you go through me.
Let's go, Fazal.
Please.

96
00:09:18,658 --> 00:09:20,888
Keep your mouth shut.
I can save your ass.

97
00:09:22,028 --> 00:09:24,724
Go, go. Up, up. Come on.

98
00:09:26,966 --> 00:09:28,991
<i>Everybody move.</i>

99
00:09:32,405 --> 00:09:35,670
In the truck.
Everybody in.

100
00:09:37,910 --> 00:09:39,741
<i>Come on. Come on.</i>

101
00:09:41,747 --> 00:09:43,840
<i>[Foreign Language]</i>

102
00:09:48,054 --> 00:09:50,113
<i>Nice move, Mike.
[Machine Guns Firing]</i>

103
00:09:50,189 --> 00:09:52,180
Give me a heads-up next time?

104
00:09:56,095 --> 00:09:58,586
<i>[ Chattering]</i>

105
00:09:58,664 --> 00:10:03,192
<i>Understand I want him
to keep his mouth shut.
Just tell him to be quiet.</i>

106
00:10:03,269 --> 00:10:06,534
<i>[Wayne]
I know that.
What do you suggest?</i>

107
00:10:12,912 --> 00:10:15,710
You okay?
Yeah.

108
00:10:15,781 --> 00:10:18,875
So, what are we gonna do?

109
00:10:18,951 --> 00:10:23,115
Never mind about that.
Go inside. Keep warm.
Make some coffee or somethin'. Go on.

110
00:10:56,889 --> 00:10:58,754
Three.

111
00:11:14,807 --> 00:11:16,866
Some change, man?

112
00:11:16,942 --> 00:11:18,933
<i>[Horn Honks]</i>

113
00:11:20,646 --> 00:11:24,912
<i>[Man]
''I'm sorry''? That's all he can say?
''I'm sorry''?</i>

114
00:11:24,984 --> 00:11:28,511
These people will be gone in a week.
The mayor... Have you heard of
creative development?

115
00:11:28,587 --> 00:11:30,851
We've been with
your institution for 35 years.

116
00:11:30,923 --> 00:11:33,289
Okay, fine.
You can talk to my lawyer.

117
00:11:35,995 --> 00:11:37,929
They foreclosed on us.

118
00:11:37,997 --> 00:11:41,398
[Sighs]
They... They can't do that.
We've sold 15 units.

119
00:11:41,467 --> 00:11:43,697
That still leaves
most of the units unsold,

120
00:11:43,769 --> 00:11:46,135
and we haven't got the cash
to complete the renovation.

121
00:11:46,205 --> 00:11:48,435
One more month.
They gotta give us
just one more month.

122
00:11:48,507 --> 00:11:51,305
<i>That's it, Ben. It's over.
It's not our building anymore.</i>

123
00:11:51,377 --> 00:11:53,868
The bank owns our asses.

124
00:11:53,946 --> 00:11:56,210
Damn it!

125
00:11:56,282 --> 00:11:58,910
I can't believe it.
Just one more month.

126
00:12:00,653 --> 00:12:02,814
What are you gonna do now?

127
00:12:14,400 --> 00:12:16,459
[Car Alarm Chirps]

128
00:12:22,074 --> 00:12:23,769
<i>[Man]
Wranglers.</i>

129
00:12:25,745 --> 00:12:28,942
- Levis.
- Do you have licensing agreements
for those, dad?

130
00:12:30,783 --> 00:12:33,843
[Chuckles]
Well, they got the labels
on them, don't they?

131
00:12:35,821 --> 00:12:39,757
How's business?
Oh, you'd be proud of me.

132
00:12:39,825 --> 00:12:42,794
I proved you can lose money
in real estate.

133
00:12:42,862 --> 00:12:44,295
How much?

134
00:12:45,998 --> 00:12:49,957
Round figures?
Round figures, square figures...
whatever.

135
00:12:51,337 --> 00:12:53,305
Everything.

136
00:12:54,373 --> 00:12:58,503
So, I guess an M.B.A. From Wharton
doesn't make you any smarter
than the old man, huh?

137
00:12:58,577 --> 00:13:01,546
You can...
[Chuckles]
You can start with these.

138
00:13:03,015 --> 00:13:04,949
Catch you later.

139
00:13:12,224 --> 00:13:14,385
[Chattering]

140
00:13:20,232 --> 00:13:23,167
[Mike]
We're not here because we want to
mess with your country.

141
00:13:23,235 --> 00:13:25,226
You can keep it, pal.
[Laughs]

142
00:13:26,405 --> 00:13:31,672
You want to live in the Middle Ages
and eat a lot of goat and keep your women
tied up in sacks, you go right ahead.

143
00:13:31,744 --> 00:13:36,374
That's your privilege.
We just want to stop you
from messing with ours.

144
00:13:45,424 --> 00:13:47,415
All right.

145
00:13:49,562 --> 00:13:52,190
Fazal, why don't we do a little recap?

146
00:13:52,264 --> 00:13:55,893
We know that you
and your dead pal, Walid, run...

147
00:13:55,968 --> 00:13:58,766
a major supply route
right into the States.

148
00:13:58,838 --> 00:14:03,901
<i>Now, you can either
cut a deal with us if you want to,
or we could...</i>

149
00:14:03,976 --> 00:14:06,570
toss you back out there
to your old buddies...

150
00:14:06,645 --> 00:14:09,170
and let them bounce
rocks off of your head.

151
00:14:13,586 --> 00:14:15,110
Please.

152
00:14:17,489 --> 00:14:21,550
We need to clear out this garbage,
sell these machines,
take the write-down.

153
00:14:21,627 --> 00:14:23,788
Who's gonna buy 'em?
We couldn't give 'em away.

154
00:14:23,863 --> 00:14:26,354
We'd have to hire somebody
to haul 'em off as scrap.

155
00:14:26,432 --> 00:14:29,094
We don't make anything
here anymore.

156
00:14:29,168 --> 00:14:32,296
We design it, but it's...
it's cut and fit together
someplace else.

157
00:14:32,371 --> 00:14:35,704
Then we stick the label on it
and ship it off to the retailer.
That's all.

158
00:14:35,774 --> 00:14:39,369
It's called ''globalization.''
They never taught you that at school?

159
00:14:39,445 --> 00:14:42,608
Anyway, here,
we got a real problem.

160
00:14:42,681 --> 00:14:44,808
<i>[Horn Honks]</i>

161
00:14:55,561 --> 00:15:00,294
<i>I got 30,000 linen shirts coming
from Shanghai for the Shirt Palace.</i>

162
00:15:00,366 --> 00:15:04,029
Six buttons, tab collars,
twin pleat, square cut.

163
00:15:04,103 --> 00:15:06,628
Only problem is
nobody seems to know
where they are.

164
00:15:06,705 --> 00:15:08,673
Could be a shipping problem.

165
00:15:08,741 --> 00:15:11,209
Could be a Customs problem.

166
00:15:11,277 --> 00:15:13,268
But I know a guy.

167
00:15:13,345 --> 00:15:15,905
You always did.

168
00:15:15,981 --> 00:15:17,972
<i>[ Chattering]</i>

169
00:15:26,492 --> 00:15:28,517
<i>[ Cell Phone Rings]</i>

170
00:15:28,594 --> 00:15:30,994
<i>[Man]
You kiddin'me?
This fool drives an Acura.</i>

171
00:15:31,063 --> 00:15:34,499
<i>So, I say,
''Okay, come back over to my garage,
you check out my Porsche. ''</i>

172
00:15:34,566 --> 00:15:37,160
<i>- All right?
- [Man #2] Get out of my way.</i>

173
00:15:39,772 --> 00:15:43,538
<i>- How you doin'?
- What can I do for you?</i>

174
00:15:43,609 --> 00:15:47,204
I really appreciate you giving me
a few minutes of your time.
Yeah.

175
00:15:47,279 --> 00:15:50,009
I got a little shipping problem
I need some help with.

176
00:15:50,082 --> 00:15:53,518
<i>Shipping problem?
What is it? Customs?
I don't know.</i>

177
00:15:53,585 --> 00:15:55,519
Well, who's your shipper?
Greater Orient.

178
00:15:55,587 --> 00:15:58,317
Yeah. So what can I do for you?

179
00:15:58,390 --> 00:16:02,121
Well, if you could make a phone call
for me, talk to somebody.

180
00:16:02,194 --> 00:16:06,563
Yeah. Um, I could probably
do that for you. Let me find you
another shipper though.

181
00:16:06,632 --> 00:16:10,830
You hungry?
You want something to eat?
No. Uh, this is my son Ben.

182
00:16:10,903 --> 00:16:13,872
I'm bringing him into the business.
Hmm.

183
00:16:13,939 --> 00:16:16,874
Show him what the real world
is like after grad school.

184
00:16:16,942 --> 00:16:18,876
Real world.
Real world.

185
00:16:18,944 --> 00:16:20,878
Good. I'll see
what I can do for you.

186
00:16:20,946 --> 00:16:24,939
If you can do anything... anything at all.
Good to see you, Alex.

187
00:16:25,017 --> 00:16:27,008
Yeah.

188
00:16:27,086 --> 00:16:29,520
All right. Take care.

189
00:16:34,827 --> 00:16:38,923
In my village, the poppy is how we live.

190
00:16:39,999 --> 00:16:43,366
What other crop will you grow
to feed your family?

191
00:16:43,435 --> 00:16:46,836
The government offers you
$250 an acre...

192
00:16:46,905 --> 00:16:49,840
to grow something else.

193
00:16:49,908 --> 00:16:55,312
<i>But the poppy can bring you $2,000.</i>

194
00:16:56,315 --> 00:16:58,306
You see?

195
00:17:02,821 --> 00:17:04,846
<i>Why don't you cut the bull?</i>

196
00:17:04,923 --> 00:17:07,687
You're not a farmer.
You're a player.

197
00:17:07,760 --> 00:17:12,697
You and your buddy,
wholesaling truckloads of the stuff.

198
00:17:19,304 --> 00:17:21,636
I know about you.

199
00:17:22,841 --> 00:17:24,775
<i>[Man]
Well, we're wasting our time here.</i>

200
00:17:27,146 --> 00:17:29,205
So, uh,

201
00:17:29,281 --> 00:17:31,977
Fazal, why don't you let us know
when you want to...

202
00:17:32,051 --> 00:17:34,110
pull your turban
out of your ass?

203
00:18:01,847 --> 00:18:04,077
<i>[Ben]
Who was that punk?</i>

204
00:18:04,149 --> 00:18:07,516
<i>He's a guy who can help.
It's called ''guanxi. ''</i>

205
00:18:07,586 --> 00:18:10,419
Right now I need a favor from him.

206
00:18:10,489 --> 00:18:12,923
<i>One day,
he'll need a favor from me.</i>

207
00:18:12,991 --> 00:18:16,620
He's a middleman.
I go to him, he makes a phone call.

208
00:18:16,695 --> 00:18:20,131
Somebody else makes a phone call,
and our container gets expedited.

209
00:18:20,199 --> 00:18:24,363
It's how things get done.
What are you getting into here, dad?
Tongs, triads?

210
00:18:24,436 --> 00:18:27,030
Keep your voice down.

211
00:18:27,106 --> 00:18:29,700
In this business you sometimes
have to cut corners...

212
00:18:29,775 --> 00:18:32,039
<i>and hold your nose
while you're doing it.</i>

213
00:18:40,252 --> 00:18:43,779
[Gurgling]

214
00:18:49,361 --> 00:18:51,352
Look.

215
00:18:53,532 --> 00:18:56,296
That's what I owe ya, okay?
All right.

216
00:18:56,368 --> 00:18:58,700
Bonus. Here.

217
00:19:00,572 --> 00:19:04,338
[Sighs]
I... I think we should
tell the cops about...

218
00:19:04,409 --> 00:19:06,877
About what?
About the guy.

219
00:19:06,945 --> 00:19:08,879
<i>What guy?</i>

220
00:19:08,947 --> 00:19:11,415
<i>The dead body
we pulled out of the ocean.
Listen, Dale.</i>

221
00:19:11,483 --> 00:19:14,714
A fishing boat can be
a pretty dangerous place.
You know what I mean?

222
00:19:14,786 --> 00:19:19,052
You want to learn the ropes,
this would be a really good time
for you to start.

223
00:19:21,393 --> 00:19:23,691
Here.
No.

224
00:19:23,762 --> 00:19:25,696
No. Here, here.
Go get laid.

225
00:19:25,764 --> 00:19:29,723
And if anybody asks ya
how the fishing was,
you know what to say, don't ya?

226
00:19:29,801 --> 00:19:32,531
Yeah. Good.

227
00:19:53,992 --> 00:19:55,960
Take a break.

228
00:19:56,028 --> 00:19:58,053
Enjoy yourself.

229
00:19:59,364 --> 00:20:01,355
<i>It's Fashion Week.</i>

230
00:20:02,434 --> 00:20:04,425
<i>[Thunder Rumbling]</i>

231
