301
00:25:47,045 --> 00:25:48,979
Hmm? Sit down.

302
00:26:09,034 --> 00:26:10,831
[Giggling]

303
00:26:14,573 --> 00:26:18,270
Adam, is going to be okay.
She is going to love it.

304
00:26:22,814 --> 00:26:25,840
It's a start.
Yes.

305
00:26:27,252 --> 00:26:29,186
Yeah.

306
00:26:29,654 --> 00:26:31,246
<i>[Seagull Squawking]</i>

307
00:26:33,024 --> 00:26:34,958
[Chattering]

308
00:26:38,597 --> 00:26:40,690
<i>[Man]
You got it?</i>

309
00:26:45,003 --> 00:26:47,494
Hey, look. Floater.

310
00:26:50,442 --> 00:26:51,431
<i>[Man]
Where?</i>

311
00:26:54,412 --> 00:26:56,346
Under the pier.

312
00:27:12,731 --> 00:27:14,722
Looks good.

313
00:27:26,277 --> 00:27:28,768
[Over Radio]
It's a freighter.

314
00:27:30,215 --> 00:27:32,479
I see a gash
on the port side.

315
00:27:33,718 --> 00:27:36,414
It's opened the forward bulkheads.

316
00:27:36,488 --> 00:27:38,752
Any sign of leaking oil?

317
00:27:38,823 --> 00:27:41,690
Not so far.

318
00:27:41,760 --> 00:27:43,751
I'll take a closer look.

319
00:27:48,466 --> 00:27:52,266
