off the coast.

350
00:30:30,461 --> 00:30:32,656
So?

351
00:30:32,730 --> 00:30:36,257
Were they on that ship?
I don't know what
you're talking about.

352
00:30:37,335 --> 00:30:39,735
My wife and daughter
are coming in this week, yes?

353
00:30:41,239 --> 00:30:43,230
They're coming.

354
00:30:44,909 --> 00:30:46,843
Just tell me.

355
00:30:46,911 --> 00:30:50,039
Look. I run a cab company.

356
00:30:50,114 --> 00:30:52,275
''Airport? Twenty minutes?
Yes, sir. Right away.''

357
00:30:52,350 --> 00:30:55,808
Sometimes I put people
in touch with other people.

358
00:30:55,887 --> 00:30:58,879
It's a sideline, okay?
I like to help people.

359
00:30:58,957 --> 00:31:01,448
But I'm just the middleman.
That's all.

360
00:31:02,460 --> 00:31:04,951
Get out of my office. Please.

361
00:31:09,567 --> 00:31:12,365
Are they dead?
My wife and daughter?

362
00:31:12,437 --> 00:31:14,905
This is not my concern.

363
00:31:14,973 --> 00:31:16,941
Please, please.

364
00:31:18,009 --> 00:31:21,274
Look. I did you a favor.
Now you do me a favor.

365
00:31:21,346 --> 00:31:23,337
Leave me alone.

366
00:31:24,616 --> 00:31:27,084
Were they aboard that ship?

367
00:31:27,151 --> 00:31:29,642
What happened?
The ship can't go down like this.

368
00:31:29,721 --> 00:31:32,849
What... What happened?
I'll look into it.

369
00:31:43,301 --> 00:31:45,735
<i>[Phone Rings]
[ Chattering]</i>

370
00:32:04,422 --> 00:32:06,413
<i>[Mike]
Hey.</i>

371
00:32:07,558 --> 00:32:09,856
Why don't you guys, uh,
take a break, huh?

372
00:32:48,833 --> 00:32:50,892
Aaah!

373
00:32:54,405 --> 00:32:58,136
A couple weeks back
a friend of mine was out in the boonies.

374
00:32:58,209 --> 00:33:02,236
<i>Special Forces,
doing a sweep for weapons,
ammunition dumps.</i>

375
00:33:03,581 --> 00:33:06,243
<i>They ran into some Al-Qaeda.</i>

376
00:33:06,317 --> 00:33:08,308
<i>[Machine Gun Fires]</i>

377
00:33:09,320 --> 00:33:13,984
Now he found where the Taliban had stored
the opium that they'd confiscated
when they were in power.

378
00:33:15,326 --> 00:33:18,591
<i>There's a cave filled with it.</i>

379
00:33:18,663 --> 00:33:20,722
It's piled...

380
00:33:20,798 --> 00:33:22,823
It's piled to the roof.

381
00:33:35,947 --> 00:33:38,211
It's still there.

382
00:33:39,283 --> 00:33:41,843
<i>He destroyed access to the cave.</i>

383
00:33:47,158 --> 00:33:50,457
What do you think
a cave full of opium is worth?

384
00:33:54,132 --> 00:33:56,123
- To Uncle Sam?
- No.

385
00:33:56,200 --> 00:33:58,566
To the two people who, uh...

386
00:33:58,636 --> 00:34:00,570
who know about it.

387
00:34:00,638 --> 00:34:02,572
You and me.

388
00:34:02,640 --> 00:34:04,608
And the man who found it?

389
00:34:04,675 --> 00:34:06,700
Your friend?
Don't worry about him.

390
00:34:06,778 --> 00:34:08,769
He got killed.

391
00:34:10,014 --> 00:34:13,211
After he told me about it,
somebody booby-trapped
his rucksacks.

392
00:34:15,386 --> 00:34:18,480
As an American, you really gotta
watch your back around here.

393
00:34:20,558 --> 00:34:22,719
<i>It's just you and me.</i>

394
00:34:22,794 --> 00:34:25,262
Don't you guys have this saying...

395
00:34:25,329 --> 00:34:28,958
''Me against my brother,
my brother and me
against my cousins,

396
00:34:29,033 --> 00:34:31,331
and my cousins and me
against the world,'' hmm?

397
00:34:39,744 --> 00:34:42,338
We're gonna need to
get the stuff off the mountain.

398
00:34:42,413 --> 00:34:46,406
We're gonna need
trucks and planes
to get it out of the country.

399
00:34:46,484 --> 00:34:48,952
We need people
we can trust to guard it...

400
00:34:49,020 --> 00:34:52,820
and informants to let us know
if somebody's trying to take it off us...

401
00:34:52,890 --> 00:34:56,519
and to bribe people...
to look the other way.

402
00:34:56,594 --> 00:34:58,858
<i>And you would trust me?
No.</i>

403
00:34:58,930 --> 00:35:00,921
Not a chance, man.

404
00:35:00,998 --> 00:35:02,989
I'll be there with you.

405
00:35:04,836 --> 00:35:08,203
'Cause I'm the only one
who knows where the stuff is.

406
00:35:13,744 --> 00:35:16,804
Okay, here it is.

407
00:35:16,881 --> 00:35:19,281
Ta-da.

408
00:35:19,350 --> 00:35:21,113
<i>Okay, do you want to carve it?</i>

409
00:35:23,054 --> 00:35:26,148
All right. Good.

410
00:35:46,544 --> 00:35:48,671
